      "writtenOn": "2019-06-13T18:24:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve learned about https://github.com/git/git/blob/a42d7b6a5b5addcce01f483547ad96825c7a96e0/Documentation/config.txt#L1733 today. Maybe  we can use it instead of git credential helper to provide OAuth tokens. Then we can get rid of known_gerrit_hosts setting completely.\n\nThere are some issues though. This setting applies blankly. Fetching non-gob repos (like github) will fail. Also running \"git config -l --global\" will leak access token to logs.\n\nAnother termonuclear option I was considering is write our \"own\" protocol that injects tokens (sort of like gob\u0027s persistent-https://) and use insteadOf rewrite https://* \u003d\u003e our-own-https://*.",
